cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about Chinese word segmentation using neural network-based methods, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes two methods to exploit dictionary information, which involves machine learning techniques such as pseudo labeled data generation and multi-task learning. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR is also a possible sub-category.
